  "texts": [
    "This feedback was obtained by using the image itself.",
    "The model was assessed by training the platform on two open datasets, the Chaos 2019 and the LiTS 2017, each with a different imbalance ratio and imaging modality.",
    "On well-known abdominal imaging benchmarks, the suggested Ensemble-GAN architecture outperformed competing approaches in the semantic segmentation of healthcare pictures.",
    "The semantic segmentation accuracy of the healthy liver left and right kidneys, spleen, and F1 score was 0.93, 0.96, 0.90, and 0.94, respectively.",
    "For segmenting the lesions and liver simultaneously, the total F1 values were 0.83 and 0.94, accordingly.Larsson et al. [63] contrasted convex-concave min-max settings with optimization techniques that actually converge when training GANs using SGDA and Adam."
  ]
